I"Ø<h2 id="details">Details</h2>

<p>This is where youâ€™ll add and populate your environmental variables file for GitLab.</p>

<h2 id="instructions">Instructions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Add the following section to your environment variable file. This is the same file mentioned <a href="env-var-setup-guide.html">in step 2</a>. Adding the following variables allows the agent to access your GitLab data:
    <p class="code-block"><code>
     GITLAB_TOKEN=...
 </code></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a personal access token in GitLab, following the instructions <a href="https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/profile/personal_access_tokens.html#creating-a-personal-access-token">here</a>. Use this token as the value for <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">GITLAB_TOKEN</code>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>If you have additional systems not yet configured in your environment variable file, refer back to <a href="env-var-setup-guide.html">step 2</a> to set up your other systems.</li>
</ol>
